msgctxt "mn150:5.7"
msgid ""
"Tasmā te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā sakkātabbā garukātabbā mānetabbā pūjetabbā."
msgstr "That’s why they deserve honor, respect, reverence, and veneration."

msgctxt "mn150:5.8"
msgid "Ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā sotaviññeyyesu saddesu …"
msgstr ""
"There are ascetics and brahmins who are free of greed, hate, and delusion "
"for sounds known by the ear …"

msgctxt "mn150:5.9"
msgid "ghānaviññeyyesu gandhesu …"
msgstr "smells known by the nose …"

msgctxt "mn150:5.10"
msgid "jivhāviññeyyesu rasesu …"
msgstr "tastes known by the tongue …"

msgctxt "mn150:5.11"
msgid "kāyaviññeyyesu phoṭṭhabbesu …"
msgstr "touches known by the body …"

msgctxt "mn150:5.12"
msgid ""
"manoviññeyyesu dhammesu vītarāgā vītadosā vītamohā, ajjhattaṃ "
"vūpasantacittā, samacariyaṃ caranti kāyena vācāya manasā, evarūpā "
"samaṇabrāhmaṇā sakkātabbā garukātabbā mānetabbā pūjetabbā."
msgstr ""
"thoughts known by the mind, who are peaceful inside, and who conduct "
"themselves well by way of body, speech, and mind. They deserve honor, "
"respect, reverence, and veneration."

msgctxt "mn150:5.13"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "mn150:5.14"
msgid ""
"Mayampi hi manoviññeyyesu dhammesu avītarāgā avītadosā avītamohā ajjhattaṃ "
"avūpasantacittā, samavisamaṃ carāma kāyena vācāya manasā, tesaṃ no "
"samacariyampi hetaṃ uttari passataṃ."
msgstr ""
