#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.293"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
#. VAR: pana vo → sace te (s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "mn150:6.1"
msgid "Sace pana vo, gahapatayo, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ puccheyyuṃ:"
msgstr "If wanderers who follow other paths were to ask you:"

msgctxt "mn150:6.2"
msgid ""
"‘ke panāyasmantānaṃ ākārā, ke anvayā, yena tumhe āyasmanto evaṃ vadetha?"
msgstr ""
"‘But what reasons and evidence do you have regarding those venerables that "
"justifies saying:"

msgctxt "mn150:6.3"
msgid ""
"Addhā te āyasmanto vītarāgā vā rāgavinayāya vā paṭipannā, vītadosā vā "
"dosavinayāya vā paṭipannā, vītamohā vā mohavinayāya vā paṭipannā’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Clearly those venerables are free of greed, hate, and delusion, or "
"practicing to be free of them’?"

msgctxt "mn150:6.4"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ puṭṭhā tumhe, gahapatayo, tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ evaṃ "
"byākareyyātha:"
msgstr "You should answer them:"

msgctxt "mn150:6.5"
msgid ""
"‘tathā hi te āyasmanto araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevanti."
msgstr ""
"‘It’s because those venerables frequent remote lodgings in the wilderness "
"and the forest."

msgctxt "mn150:6.6"
msgid ""
"Natthi kho pana tattha tathārūpā cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā ye disvā disvā "
"abhirameyyuṃ, natthi kho pana tattha tathārūpā sotaviññeyyā saddā ye sutvā "
"sutvā abhirameyyuṃ, natthi kho pana tattha tathārūpā ghānaviññeyyā gandhā ye "
"ghāyitvā ghāyitvā abhirameyyuṃ, natthi kho pana tattha tathārūpā "
"jivhāviññeyyā rasā ye sāyitvā sāyitvā abhirameyyuṃ, natthi kho pana tattha "
"tathārūpā kāyaviññeyyā phoṭṭhabbā ye phusitvā phusitvā abhirameyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"In such places there are no sights known by the eye to see and enjoy. there "
"are no sounds known by the ear to hear and enjoy, no odors known by the nose "
"to smell and enjoy, no flavors known by the tongue to taste and enjoy, and "
"no touches known by the body to feel and enjoy."

#. VAR: yena mayaṃ → yena mayaṃ āyasmanto (bj, pts1) | yena mayaṃ āyasmante (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "mn150:6.7"
msgid "Ime kho no, āvuso, ākārā, ime anvayā, yena mayaṃ evaṃ vadema—"
msgstr ""
"These are the reasons and evidence that you have regarding those venerables "
"that justifies saying:"

msgctxt "mn150:6.8"
msgid ""
"addhā te āyasmanto vītarāgā vā rāgavinayāya vā paṭipannā, vītadosā vā "
"dosavinayāya vā paṭipannā, vītamohā vā mohavinayāya vā paṭipannā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Clearly those venerables are free of greed, hate, and delusion, or "
"practicing to be free of them.’"

msgctxt "mn150:6.9"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ puṭṭhā tumhe, gahapatayo, tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ evaṃ "
"byākareyyāthā”ti."
msgstr ""
"When questioned by wanderers who follow other paths, that’s how you should "
"answer them.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya7"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn150:7.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, nagaravindeyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"When he had spoken, the brahmins and householders of Nagaravinda said to the "
"Buddha:"

msgctxt "mn150:7.2"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama."
msgstr "“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent!"

msgctxt "mn150:7.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bho gotama, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā "
"vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya:"
" ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhotā gotamena anekapariyāyena "
"dhammo pakāsito."
msgstr ""
"As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing "
"out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good "
"eyes can see what’s there, Master Gotama has made the Teaching clear in many "
"ways."

msgctxt "mn150:7.4"
msgid ""
"Ete mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāma dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca."
msgstr ""
"We go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant "
"Saṅgha."

msgctxt "mn150:7.5"
msgid "Upāsake no bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupete saraṇaṃ gate”ti."
msgstr ""
"From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember us as lay followers who have "
"gone for refuge for life.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn150:7.6"
msgid "Nagaravindeyyasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
